name: حيّ جميل
description:
حي جميل هو موطن جدة للفنون، وصُمم ليضم مجموعة واسعة من التخصصات الإبداعية في وجهة واحدة ليكون مركزًا مجتمعيًا ديناميكيًا وإبداعيًا، ويشمل سينما حي للأفلام المستقلة ومعارض فنون حي ومستكشفي حي للصغار المبدعين، ومساحات متعددة الأغراض للعروض المختلفة مثل ورش العمل والمناقشات، بالإضافة إلى مقاهي ومطعم وساحة مجتمعية متاحة للجميع.

Hayy Jameel is Jeddah's dedicated home for the arts, conceived as a dynamic, creative, community hub. Hayy Jameel is home to Hayy Cinema, exhibition spaces, Hayy Explorers, a creative space for children and young adults, multi-purpose spaces for performances, workshops and talks, cafes and eateries as well as Saha, a central community courtyard.

name: متحف العلوم والتقنية في الإسلام
description:
The Museum celebrates the contributions of Muslim scholars to science and technology during the first Golden Age of Islam from the 650 to 1650. These Muslim scholars include amongst them the great scientists, inventors, engineers, mathematicians and teachers of that time, such as Jabir ibn Hayyan, Abbas bin Firnas, al-Kindi, al-Razi, al-Jazari and Taqi al-Din.

The Museum demonstrates how their contributions shaped the world as we know it today and how their pioneering work laid the foundation for modern civilization. The benefits of their work are all around us today.

description:
Hafez Gallery was founded in 2014 in the city of Jeddah. We exhibit art from Saudi Arabia and the Middle East. And we seek to share our art culture in local and foreign forums. Going forward, we pledge to reinvest our profits fully into our cultural and educational programs.

name: متحف مدينة الطيبات العالمية للعلوم والمعرفة
description:
The museum located in Jeddah is a cultural institution that showcases the rich history and heritage of the city. The museum is dedicated to preserving and promoting the arts, culture, and traditions of the people of Saudi. It is a must-visit destination for anyone interested in learning about the history and culture of Saudi Arabia.
The exhibits are organized into different sections, each focusing on a specific aspect of Jeddah's culture and history.
One of the most popular exhibits is the section dedicated to traditional Saudi Arabian clothing. Here, visitors can see examples of traditional clothing worn by men and women in different regions of Saudia Arabia
